### HTTP Not Redirecting to HTTPS

Symptoms: - Accessing http://service.lab.local doesn't redirect - Must manually type https: - Mixed content warnings Cause: Missing HTTP redirect block in Nginx configuration Diagnosis: ```bash # Check Nginx config docker exec nginx cat /etc/nginx/nginx.conf | grep “return 301” # If empty: redirect is missing ``` Solution: Add redirect block to nginx.conf: ```nginx server { listen 80; server_name service.lab.local; return 301 https:$host$request_uri; } ```

Restart Nginx: ```bash docker compose restart nginx ```

Test redirect: ```bash curl -I http://service.lab.local # Should show: 301 Moved Permanently # Location: https://service.lab.local/ ```

