### “docker compose restart” Doesn't Apply Volume Changes

Symptoms: - Added volume mount to docker-compose.yml - Ran `docker compose restart` - Container still can't see mounted files

Cause: `restart` command reuses existing container with old configuration

Diagnosis: ```bash # Check container mount points docker inspect nginx | grep -A 10 “Mounts” # Old mounts still present ```

Solution:

Volume changes require container recreation: ```bash docker compose down docker compose up -d ```

Not: ```bash docker compose restart # This won't work for volume changes ```

Prevention: Remember: restart = reload config, down/up = recreate container

—

### Certificate Expired

Symptoms: - Browser shows “NET::ERR_CERT_DATE_INVALID” - Services show certificate expiration warning

Cause: Certificate validity period exceeded (2 years)

Diagnosis: ```bash # Check certificate expiration sudo openssl x509 -in /etc/nginx/ssl/hostname.crt -noout -dates ```

Solution:

1. Generate new CSR with same private key 2. Sign CSR with FreeIPA CA 3. Replace old certificate 4. Restart Nginx

See SSL/TLS Management Guide for detailed renewal procedure.

Prevention: Set calendar reminder 30 days before expiration

